First, monetizing its AI work through an API makes sense for Google, as its=
 not disruptive to its Search business model. Second, Google gets a major c=
ustomer that can function as a showpiece for their capabilities. Third, it=
=E2=80=99s clear that coding is one of the most important applications for =
AI today, but the best possible experience is going to come by integrating =
AI with an IDE, and Google doesn=E2=80=99t have an IDE for general purpose =
use; now its AI is going to be incorporated in an already large and very ra=
